// Linked List Concept:
//
// A linked list is a linear data structure where elements (nodes) are stored non-contiguously,
// and each node contains a data field and a reference (link) to the next node.
//
// Applications:
// - Dynamic memory allocation
// - Implementing stacks, queues
// - Graph adjacency representation
// - Performing arithmetic on big integers
// - Real-time systems where memory efficiency matters
